usage: git cleanex [<options>]

Clean untracked and ignored files.

    -h|--help               display help
    .                       visit startup module only (do not visit submodules)
    -f|--force              clean even if work dir is dirty
    -d|--dsm-only           delete dangling submodules only
    <git-for options>       options for 'git for'
    
example:
    git cleanex             # delete ignored files (stop if repo dirty)
    git cleanex -f          # delete ignored files and dangling submodules
    git cleanex -d          # clean dangling submodules only
